Stratocratic-Anarchy Oceanic Empire wrote:After the definitely not wasted meeting,

Supreme Man teleports back to Earth. As he flies across the Labrador Sea heading back to Greenland, Supreme Man is hit by a missile from a Catgirl combat drone UCAV. Supreme Man lifts up his hand and closes it into a fist which causes the drone to explode in a flurry of fire (Supreme Man can use telekinesis). However, his senses detect thousands of more combat drones all around him.

As he swings his fists around and uses energy blasts to take down the combat drones. His senses pick up something else. The Halo Theme plays loudly all around him. What is happening?

At this point he lets the drones ram into him which don't damage him because he is a multiversal god. His curiosity is intensified. Why is there Halo music playing?

And then a figure teleports in front of him. Chimichanga. Of the former Burrito Republic.

"Hmph," Supreme Man mutters. "You are hard to kill, Burrito Chimichanga. How about this. I will give you a seat with me to guide the Multiverse to its greatest potential. There will be no more divisions. No more hardship. And no more death and chaos. Together, we will do glorious things. Join me."

But Burrito Chimichanga shakes his head. "You slaughter zillions for nothing. Instead of protecting the Multiverse as you created yourself to be, you are destroying it. And now we will do all we can to stop you. You killed my people in utter cold blood. We will have no mercy on you." Then as Burrito lunges towards Supreme Man to try and punch him, he disappears into dust.

Supreme Man smiles. "You're teleportation skills are good. But it won't be enough."

Supreme Man braces himself to chase after Chimichanga but sees a massive armada of ships of the Algerbil Alliance approaching him. He sends a telepathic message to the Catalan Council of Freedom in Nuuk to not send any support units for Supreme Man. He wishes to fight the Algerbil Alliance in the Labrador Sea of the Atlantic alone. He wants to see how much resolve these puny weaklings have.

The background music changes to literal battle music (use your imagination and choose which song you think would fit the battle) and Supreme Man becomes a glowing figure in front of the Algerbil Armada.

Supreme Commander M'yri'ah of the Catgirl Republic orders for the first strike on Lord Veemaa Abelló II aka Supreme Man. "Fire!" she calls. And immediately a massive barrage of missiles from the armada chase after Supreme Man.

Supreme Man laughs irrationally and he quickly forms a hundred-layer electronic shield around him. The missiles do basically nothing to the shield. But a barrage from a large Capuchin-based battleship fires a powerful shell at Mach 28 which damages half of the shield. Supreme Man is impressed but it's barely enough to scare him. And so he lifts the battleship utilizing telekinesis which shocks the entire fleet. However, M'yri'ah is still willing to continue the fight.

"Deploy the 'craft!"

Hundreds upon hundreds of fighter jets, helicopters, attack jets, stratosphere aircraft, and versatile spacecraft throw themselves towards Supreme Man. They travel at gusting speeds but Supreme Man isn't impressed. Instead, he drops the Capuchin battleship he was lifting up and focuses himself on the fight with the aircraft. Naval artillery from all the warships fire on Supreme Man, but they barely do a scratch on him.

Supreme Man creates himself a hundred arms in a second. And proceeds to stretch these arms beyond infinity. The aircraft have a hard time maneuvering out of the way of the bundle of arms and many of them crash and become balls of fire when they hit the arms. Supreme Man laughs and then begins mentally manipulating the pilots, which causes many of them to start attacking the Algerbil Alliance fleet. The fleet, however, continues to fight strongly.

The fight continues for hours. Supreme Man consistently makes fun of M'yri'ah and the rest of the Algerbil Alliance as he taunts the warships and continuously manipulates mentally the minds of some of the officers. Many of the officers have throbbing headaches from the battle because of Supreme Man's constant manipulation of the mind.

However, a message arrives for M'yri'ah after she orders another barrage of jets to staff attack Supreme Man to divert his attention away from the fleet.

H E L P I S C O M I N G


Detection systems detect a powerful energy signature coming from the South Atlantic.

M'yri'ah smiles.

The atmosphere suddenly changes into a purple glow. Supreme Man is shocked. His eyes gaze sternly in front of him.

Chimichanga and Uno Reverse Savior stand face to face with Supreme Man. But something else shocks Supreme Man.

"Master Man?!"

Supreme Man eyes his apprentice in shock. He was alive! "What are you doing here, Master Man?! You were dead one second and now you're here!"

Master Man smiles. "I learned your tricks. How to pull off illusions. Meet Giselle, the clone of my former apprentice Woman."

A woman hovers next to Master Man with a blazing purple aura and amethyst-colored eyes. She smiles.

"I know everything about you Supreme Man. This collapse of reality you wish to bring will not come to pass. Your belief in committing genocide to bring a new order to the multiverse will not happen. This universe will now remain under our protection. The Gods of Reality."

Supreme Man is furious. "This sentient burrito Chimichanga isn't a god! So how can you claim he is one."

"A god doesn't need to be powerful, Supreme Man. Look at the Capuchin for example. Anyhow, Chimichanga absorbed the powers of his Burrito people who were filled with the essence of the now long gone Burrito God. He is now the successor to the Burrito God. So that makes him a god."

In a gaze of fury. Supreme Man leaps at Giselle. But Uno Reverse Savior leaps in front of Giselle and punches Supreme Man hard, knocking him back two miles and shocking Supreme Man.

Giselle smiles. "Gods of Reality. Algerbil Alliance. Let's do this."

Epic fight time.

*Megalovania music intensifies
